
Terrorist bombings of the U.S. Embassies in Nairobi, Kenya and Dar es Salaam,
Tanzania on August 7 1998 killed 248 in Nairobi, and 11 in Dar es Salaam.
In Nairobi 5400 were injured and 97 fully or partially blinded. In the 76
days following the bombings evidence was gathered linking the perpetrators
to the Al Qaeda organization of Osama bin Laden, several indictments were
made and several suspects were arrested but no one had yet been brought to
trial. A key figure in the Nairobi bombing, Abdallah Mohammed Fazul, head
of Al Qaeda in Kenya, had disappeared and was still at large.
